Escada Targets Profit and Sales Growth for 2011, CEO Tells FAZ

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-06-03T15:53:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/escada-targets-profit-and-sales-growth-for-2011-ceo-tells-faz.html
     June 3 (Bloomberg) --Escada SE, the German luxury clothing
maker bought by Megha Mittal, aims to post a net profit in 2011
and expects sales growth in the high single-digit range, Chief
Executive Officer Bruno Saelzer said in an interview with
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  to be published tomorrow.  The company will likely achieve sales of more than 300
million euros ($437.5 million) in 2011 and has a long-term sales
target of 500 million euros, Saelzer told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 